# ============================================
# PROJECT: LibreChat on AWS вЂ” EC2 в†’ ECS Fargate
# ROLE: DevOps / Cloud Engineer (EPAM Interview Prep)
# ============================================

## Project Overview
This project deploys LibreChat (open-source AI chat platform) on AWS using a
progressive path: EC2 + Docker Compose for learning, ECS Fargate for production.
It demonstrates DevOps/Cloud Engineering best practices as a portfolio project
for an EPAM Cloud/DevOps Engineer interview.

The goal is NOT to over-engineer with EKS from day one. The goal is to show
pragmatic decision-making: right tool for the right stage.

## Deployment Stages

### Stage 1 вЂ” EC2 + Docker Compose (Learning / Lab)
- Single EC2 t3.medium (Ubuntu 22.04)
- LibreChat + MongoDB + Meilisearch via Docker Compose
- Access via SSM Session Manager (no SSH open)
- Bedrock via IAM Instance Profile (no static keys)
- Goal: understand LibreChat internals, validate config, iterate fast

### Stage 2 вЂ” ECS Fargate (Production)
- LibreChat container в†’ ECS Fargate service
- MongoDB в†’ DocumentDB or MongoDB Atlas
- Redis в†’ ElastiCache (sessions, rate limiting)
- Search в†’ Meilisearch on ECS or OpenSearch
- ALB + ACM + Route53 в†’ HTTPS with custom domain
- EFS в†’ shared file storage for multi-task setup
- Secrets в†’ AWS Secrets Manager (no .env files)
- CI/CD в†’ GitHub Actions (validate в†’ plan в†’ deploy)

## Architecture Stack

### Stage 1 (EC2)
- IaC: Terraform (~> 5.0 AWS provider)
- Compute: EC2 t3.medium
- Compose: Docker Compose v2 (deploy-compose.yml from LibreChat repo)
- AI Backend: AWS Bedrock (Claude 3.5 Haiku, Claude 3 Sonnet)
- Auth: IAM Instance Profile with bedrock:InvokeModel
- Access: SSM Session Manager (no port 22)

### Stage 2 (ECS)
- IaC: Terraform with terraform-aws-modules (vpc, ecs, alb)
- Compute: ECS Fargate (serverless containers)
- Database: DocumentDB 5.0 or MongoDB Atlas (M10+)
- Cache: ElastiCache Redis 7 (cluster mode off, TLS)
- Storage: EFS for persistent file mounts
- Load Balancer: ALB + HTTPS + WAF (optional)
- Secrets: AWS Secrets Manager (no env files, no hardcoded values)
- AI Backend: AWS Bedrock via task IAM Role (IRSA-equivalent on ECS)
- CI/CD: GitHub Actions
- Monitoring: CloudWatch Container Insights + Logs

